4:
Phew... That should take care of the
monsters in this area.
7: Calm down, you idiots! Quit pushing!
9:
Hey, you guys need to hightail it
outta here! A shift just happened up
ahead, and now there's a ton of
monsters swarming the place!
12:
Did you hear that? 
There are still people back there!
26: No... No... NO! None of you are right!
28:
Where is it?! Where is that filthy
monster?!
30:
*huff* *wheeze* Th-thank you. We
owe you our—
32:
Wh-what in the—your body... Are
you another monster?!
44:
Out of my way! Every last one of
you! STAY AWAY!
53:
Indeed, but that power of his is most
unusual. That light... It's turning his
body into—
63: No! Not... now! I-I must... I must...
74:
Well, looks like someone's awake.
Are you feeling better?
79:
...What do you think you're doing?
Leave me be!
82: Ahaha... I'll take that as a "yes."
87:
That body of yours... Did a monster
do this to you?
92:
Do you know something about my
curse?!
96:
I have heard of a monster that can
petrify its foes with just a glance.
100: Tell me where it is! Now!
105:
Someone's in a rush... How about
telling us your name first?
110:
...Theriol. I'm searching for the
monster that placed this crystalizing
curse on me.
113:
It disappeared after cursing me,
and no matter where I look, I can't
find it anywhere!
117:
Is that why you were in the
Kaleidoscope? I know a lot of
different monsters show up there,
but finding a specific one is like
searching for a needle in a haystac—
122:
I don't have time to think of any
other way!
126:
I see. The curse must be progressive
in nature then.
129:
While I understand your need for
urgency, I cannot condone such
rash behavior. You're racing to your
death.
133:
What I do with my life is NONE of
your business!
137:
Leave him be, Light. He's not gonna
change his mind no matter what we
say.
143:
...The monster you seek, the Stone
Salamander, is an otherworldly
monster.
152: I mean it does not exist in this world.
154:
But my companions and I possess
the means by which to transport
you to its home world... What say
you to that?
159:
You seriously gonna have this guy
join us?
163:
I cannot simply sit back and watch
him kill himself.
169:
Hmph... Who said anything about
joining you guys?! I'm fine on my
own!
172:
Well, without our help, you have no
other way to traverse worlds.
176:
...What's your game here? Are you
planning to sell my crystalized body
after I die?
180:
Um, no? Who would do something
like that...
184:
You'd be surprised... I'd say
opportunistic scum makes up the
majority of you adventurers!
188:
Whether you choose to believe us is
up to you.
193:
We also travel to different worlds.
Our trips to the Kaleidoscope are
just done to prepare for our
adventures. If you hang out with us,
you'll get information, and we'll have
an ally to help us fight.
195:
So think of it like a "you scratch our
backs, and we scratch yours"
situation.
200: *sigh* You two are way too soft.
203:
You say that, but you know you
wanna help too.
217:
Awesome. In that case, let's head
home to Starview Village. That way
we can get you settled in.
222:
"Home," huh... I have no home to go
back to...
226:
So I'll go wherever I have to in order
to achieve my goals... Be it another
world or the underworld itself!
